## Core Control Principles Embedded in This SOP

### 1) Repeatability
The close must follow a consistent structure every month.

### 2) Transparency
All numbers must be traceable to source systems and support.

### 3) Accountability
Clear ownership exists for preparation, review, and approval.

### 4) No Silent Changes
Once prepared, changes require visibility and control.

### 5) Risk Awareness
RAG and materiality determine management attention.

---

## The Close Operating Model
The framework typically includes:

- Locked master template  
- Controlled working files  
- Assumption tracking  
- Documented evidence locations  
- Defined approval workflow  

---

## Status & Risk Philosophy
Tasks progress through formal statuses and must not advance without meeting control requirements.

RAG indicators provide management with immediate visibility of execution risk.

---

## Post-Close Discipline
Adjustments after close are **exceptional**, require approval, and must maintain a full audit trail.

---

## Evidence Requirements
Every task must demonstrate:

- Source of data  
- Calculation or reconciliation  
- Journal linkage (if applicable)  
- Reviewer evidence  
- Completion date  

If it cannot be evidenced â†’ it is not complete.

---

## Typical Close Duration
The standard close cycle is approximately **10 working days**, subject to business complexity.

